==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cosmogony
<hw>Cos*mog"o*ny</hw> <pr>(-n?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Cosmogonies</plw> <pr>(-n<?/z)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>kosmogoni`a</grk>; <grk>ko`smos</grk> the world + root of
<grk>gi`gnesthai</grk> to be born: cf. F. <ets>cosmogonie</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The creation of the world or universe; a theory or account of such
creation; <as>as, the poetical <ex>cosmogony</ex> of Hesiod; the
<xex>cosmogonies</xex> of Thales, Anaxagoras, and Plato</as>.</def><--
=cosmology -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>cosmogony</qex> or creation of the world has puzzled
philosophers of all ages.</q> <rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cosmographer</ent>⟦br⟧
